<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 6:26PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Macon,
southwestern Peach and southwestern Houston Counties through 700 PM
EDT...
At 626 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Saint Louis, or 3
miles south of Fort Valley, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Marshallville, Saint Louis, Winchester, Moss Oak, Meadowdale and
Henderson.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
